STATE
v.
Teon Jamell WILLIAMS 107P17-2 Supreme Court of North Carolina. August 14, 2018 Thomas O. Lawton, III, Assistant Attorney General, Sarah Kirkman, District Attorney, for State of North Carolina. Teon Jamell Williams, Defendant-Appellant, for Williams, Teon Jamell.

The following order has been entered on the motion filed on the 10th of July 2018 by Defendant to Dismiss and/or Squash, Set Aside, Vacate the Indictments for Habitual Felon and Resentence, or Consolidate, or Run Concurrent:

"Motion Dismissed by order of the Court in conference, this the 14th of August 2018."
